<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Spokesman Welcomes `Partnership' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1201192594 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1201192594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] During a news conference held today, Mircea Geoana, 
the spokesman of Romania's Ministry of Foreign Affairs, saluted 
the proposal for a Partnership for Peace that has been accepted 
by Romania's president as a precursory step of our country's 
joining NATO as a full member. 
  The declaration presented by Geoana says that the Foreign 
Affairs Ministry will forward proposals to the government 
recommending that necessary official steps should be urgently 
taken in view of launching the Partnership for Peace and to sign 
the proposed document. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

