<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iliescu Thanks Turkish Minister for Support </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1301142494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1301142494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] This morning Romania's President Ion Iliescu 
received Turkish Health Minister Kazim Dinc. During the first 
minutes of the meeting, which was also attended by the press, 
the head of the Romanian state asked his guest to convey his 
thanks to Turkish President Suleyman Demirel for his letter in 
connection with [expressing support for] Romania's wish to join 
NATO structures. President Ion Iliescu also expressed his 
satisfaction concerning the materialization of certain joint 
actions that had been agreed with President Suleyman Demirel, 
which are beneficial for both nations. 
  For his part, the Turkish minister said that he was the 
bearer of messages conveying regards from the president and the 
prime minister of his country. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

