<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhelev, Albright Discuss Partnership for Peace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1301164894 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 13 Jan 93 </F>

<F P=103> AU1301164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today Ms. Madeleine Albright, U.S. ambassador to 
the United Nations, had a meeting with President Zhelev that 
lasted longer than planned. The subject of discussion at the 
meeting was the U.S. Partnership for Peace Initiative, which has 
already become a NATO initiative. 
  Ms. Albright delivered to President Zhelev a special letter 
on behalf of U.S. President Bill Clinton that acquainted the 
president with the general nature of the initiative. 
  On behalf of Bulgaria, President Zhelev stressed our 
country's readiness to join in this initiative. They also 
discussed the situation in the Balkans and the nature of the 
bilateral relations between Bulgaria and the United States. 
  At this moment, Ms. Albright is having talks with Prime 
Minister Professor Lyuben Berov. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

