<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Denies Differences With Zhelev </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1301181494 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1301181494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] There are no differences regarding military policy 
between the leaderships of the Defense Ministry and the Armed 
Forces and the President of the Republic, Dr. Zhelev. This is 
the official stance of the Defense Ministry, which was announced 
at the Ministry's regular news conference held in Sofia today, 
in connection with certain reports in the press regarding the 
president's decree on setting up a military office. 
  Tsvyatko Donchev, chief of the Defense Ministry Press 
Service, once again confirmed Defense Minister Aleksandrov's 
categorical refusal to comment on the letter published in the 24 
CHASA daily. 

</TEXT>

