<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   French Official Signs Deal To Update Kozloduy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1301182194 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1301182194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] France will provide financial aid to update the 
Nos. 5 and 6 Power Generating Units at the Kozloduy Nuclear 
Power Plant. This is stated in the cooperation agreement signed 
today between Electricite de France, the Bulgarian Power Supply 
Committee, and the National Electrical Company. On the French 
side, the document was signed by Mr. Remy Carle [as heard], 
deputy director general of Electricite de France and chairman of 
the World Association of Nuclear Operators -- WANO, who is 
paying an official visit to Bulgaria. 
  As already reported, yesterday Mr. Carle was in Kozloduy, 
where he familiarized himself with the work completed on 
restoring the Nos. 1 and 2 Reactor Units at the nuclear plant, 
which was also carried out with French assistance. 

</TEXT>

