<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslims Reportedly Fire From UN Barracks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301211694 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1921 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301211694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratunac, Jan 13 (TANJUG) -- The Moslems Thursday 
[13 January] fired on Serb positions from the Jusuf Dzonlic 
barracks in Sarajevo which also house some of the UN 
peacekeepers, in an obviously attempt to have the Serbs blamed 
for an attack on UNPROFOR if they answer back, Serb military 
sources report. 
  All Serb suburbs and Serb positions in the Sarajevo area 
were 
shelled by Moslems, the same sources state. Moslem forces in 
the region of the Moslem enclave Gorazde (eastern Bosnia) 
continue provocations with anti-aircraft and infantry weapons in 
the direction of the Serb positions, mainly in the direction of 
Foca. 
  Moslem artillery also shelled Serb positions and civilian 
targets in the region of Doboj (north Bosnia) in the region of 
Srbobran and Gradacac (central Bosnia) on the Bihac-Krupa line 
(northern Bosnia), and around Kladanj and Olovo (central 
Bosnia). In the four-day clashes near Olovo the Serb forces 
Thursday afternoon succeeded in repulsing the Moslem forces who 
were heading towards the town itself. 

</TEXT>

