<H3> <TI>   Bosnian Croats Block Humanitarian Convoy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301215994 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1645 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301215994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, Jan 13 (TANJUG) -- Representatives of the 
UN High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) in Sarajevo reported 
Thursday [13 January] that forces of the Bosnian Croat army HVO, 
have for the past two days been holding up a humanitarian convoy 
bringing aid to Bosnian Moslems in Maglaj, northern Bosnia. 
  They reported, according to AFP, that the column of nine 
trucks with food and medicine is blocked in Novi Seher, 10 
kilometers from Maglaj, and that the UN representative Larry 
Hollingworth is negotiating its passage with the local HVO 
commanders. They also said that the Bosnian Serb forces allowed 
the convoy to pass through their territory without any problems. 
UNHCR representatives in Sarajevo also warned about the 
extremely difficult position of the 40,000 civilians in Maglaj 
since the last convoy arrived there on October 25 last year. 

</TEXT>

