<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbian Advance Pierces Muslim Lines at Olovo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301144994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1344 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1301144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Olovo, Nisici, 13 Jan (TANJUG) -- Following 
unprecedented four-day fighting, members of the Combined Brigade 
of the Herzegovina Corps this morning managed to pierce Muslim 
defense lines in several parts of the Olovo battlefield [50 km 
north of Sarajevo on Sarajevo-Tuzla road], the brigade command 
has announced. Some Muslim units have been cut off following an 
unstoppable advance by Serb infantry and tank forces, and they 
are currently surrounded. These units keep asking for help from 
Tuzla which has not arrived because of severed communications. 
A large number of Muslim soldiers are leaving the battlefield 
in panic fleeing toward Olovo. The Muslim population from 
Krusevo and other villages near Olovo is already fleeing toward 
Tuzla. 
  The Muslim defeat can neither be helped by three rows of 
bunkers deeply dug in and covered by planks and earth by which 
Olovo and neighboring villages are surrounded. In the bloody 
four-day conflicts near Olovo, four members of the Combined 
Brigade of the Herzegovina Corps have been killed, while a few 
fighters have been wounded, three of them seriously. In the 
fighting today, up to the time when this dispatch was sent, the 
Serb side had not suffered any losses. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

