<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hungarian Foreign Minister Arrives for Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401092194 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0845 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401092194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 14 Jan--Hungarian Foreign Minister Geza 
Jeszenszky arrived in Warsaw on Friday morning. During his 
one-day visit to Poland, the Hungarian diplomat will meet 
President Lech Walesa, Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak, and the 
deputy Sejm and Senate speakers. He will also hold private talks 
with Foreign Minister Andrzej Olechowski. The Hungarian 
delegation, led by Jeszenszky, will conduct talks in the Polish 
Foreign Ministry. Bilateral relations will be discussed with 
special emphasis on the lack of progress in economic and trade 
cooperation. 

</TEXT>

