<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Olechowski, Hungary's Jeszenszky Praise Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401134794 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1317 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 14 Jan -- According to Andrzej Olechowski 
and Geza Jeszenszky, foreign ministers of Poland and Hungary, it 
is hard to imagine relations between both states being better 
than to date. In their view, Polish-Hungarian friendship can 
become an "engine" of cooperation in the Visegrad Group. 
  After talks today in the Foreign Ministry, Olechowski said 
that the excellent Polish-Hungarian political contacts can also 
be translated into economic relations. In the near future, 
businessmen of both states will prepare a report on 
possibilities for expanding economic cooperation. 
  The Polish and Hungarian foreign ministers also signed an 
agreement on cooperation between their departments, including 
cooperation between ambassadors of Poland and Hungary in third 
countries. 

</TEXT>

