<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnian Croats Support Tudjman Initiative </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401212194 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1830 
GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1401212194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mate Boban, president of the Croat republic of 
Herceg-Bosna, today convened the first session of the 
presidential council of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna. The 
council discussed to date the course of peace negotiations and 
the current military and political situation in the Croat 
republic of Herceg-Bosna and Bosnia-Herzegovina. The 
Presidential Council gave its full support to the new initiative 
launched by Franjo Tudjman, the president of the Republic of 
Croatia, in Bonn as a contractual agreement on establishing 
lasting and comprehensive peace between Croat and Bosniak-Muslim 
nations in Bosnia-Herzegovina. They also gave full support to 
President Tudjman and the negotiating team, and upheld the 
constructive efforts and proposals to end the conflict in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina during the upcoming peace talks in Geneva. 

</TEXT>

