<H3> <TI>   Serbs Reportedly Resume Shelling of Srebrenica </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1401193394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1401193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This morning, the Serbian aggressor again started 
shelling Srebrenica. The regions of (?Lihtari) and Vranik were 
shelled from the direction of Bratunac, while the residential 
areas of the town were shelled from Krvavac. One civilian was 
killed and 11 seriously wounded. This was announced by the War 
Presidency of the Srebrenica commune. 
  At about 1230, the aggressor shelled the Suceska area from 
the direction of Milici. After the shelling of all (?lines), 
the aggressor fired with anti-aircraft machine guns, guns, and 
other infantry weapons. Members of UNPROFOR [UN Protection 
Forces] in our town can confirm this attack. It has been proven 
once again that Srebrenica is not protected according to the 
provisions of the Security Council Resolutions 819 and 824. 
This was stated in a communique issued by the Srebrenica War 
Presidency. 
  Because of this, the Srebrenica War Presidency appeals once 
again to the Presidency and the Government of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, as well as the General Staff of the Army of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and UNPROFOR to require the aggressor 
strictly to observe the provisions of the agreement on the 
demilitarization of Srebrenica. 

</TEXT>

