<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croats: Government Forces `Heavily Defeated' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301194794 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1800 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1301194794 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Today, the Muslim army stepped up artillery and 
infantry attack on Novi Travnik and Busovaca in central Bosnia. 
The Croat Defense Council [HVO] has heavily defeated the Muslim 
army. Zdenko Vranjes reporting for Croatian Radio from 
Medjugorje. 
  In the course of heavy fighting in the Sofe area near Vitez, 
HVO formations have managed to recapture trenches lost in recent 
fighting. As the HVO Vitez brigade reports, a large number of 
dead Muslim soldiers have been left behind in this area 
following three days of fierce fighting. The HVO will not let 
UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] enter this area and inspect the 
site unless the Muslim side enables the peace force to launch an 
inquiry in Krizancevo Selo and Buhine Kuce, the Vitez brigade 
has announced. 
  The Muslim army today continued attacking other villages, 
too, near Vitez-Lazine and Buhine Kuce in particular. The 
Muslim army's advance has been checked in this area, too. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

