<H3> <TI>   Nordic Battalion Comes Under Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1801133794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1200 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1801133794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report from the press center of the 2d Army </F>
Corps in Celic] 
  [Excerpts] The quiet morning on 18 January turned into 
hell for residents of the Celic region earlier this morning. 
Shortly after 1000, members of the Nordic battalion arrived in 
this area. Their arrival was immediately followed by shelling 
of the settlements of Vrazici and [word indistinct] from the 
direction of Brusnica. At the same time, infantry attacks were 
launched on the northeast part of our commune, from the 
direction of (?Siljes and Kupusanik), which was supported by 
anti-aircraft machine guns and anti-aircraft guns. The infantry 
attack was preceded by a strong artillery attack on the 
settlements of Celic and Ratkovici. More than 40 122-mm 
howitzer shells were fired from the direction of Markovac. In 
addition to material damage, they also wounded (?four) people in 
(?Celic). [passage omitted] 
  The last report we received refers to an attack on the 
members of the Nordic battalion. As we were told, the chetnik 
fired five [words indistinct] directly at the armored vehicles 
of the Nordic battalion [words indistinct]. We do not have many 
details of this attack, but it confirms best the hypocrisy of 
the chetnik leader Karadzic, who promised that such incidents 
would not happen. 

