<F P=101> Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Five UNPROFOR Members Detained by Guards </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1801072494 Skopje MIC in English 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1801072494 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Five Members of UNPROFOR [UN </F>
Protection Forces] Detained in Serbia"] 
  [Text] It has been announced on 14 January in Belgrade 
that two transporters carrying members of the U.S. and Norwegian 
units of UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] in Macedonia crossed 
into Serbian territory on 13 January, near the army barracks 
Slavovec, whereby the soldiers, who did not carry any weapons, 
and did not give any resistance, were apprehended by the Serbian 
border guards. After ten hours of interrogation, they were 
returned to Macedonia at the border crossing Tabanovce. 
According to an anonymous UNPROFOR officer in Macedonia, the 
three Americans and two Norwegians were treated well by the 
Serbian border guards. "It is possible that they could have 
crossed into Serbian territory while they were trying tot save 
one of the vehicles," the officer said. Otherwise, a number of 
such incidents have occurred at this frontier, as it has not 
been strictly defined. 

</TEXT>

