<F P=101> Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Akashi Meets Gligorov, Popovski, Crvenkovski </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1401214594 Skopje MIC in English 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1401214594 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Akashi in Skopje"] </F>
  [Text] The chief of UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] and 
Special Representative of the UN Secretary General Yasushi 
Akashi arrived on a one day visit to the Republic of Macedonia. 
The fist visit of this high functionary is within the frame of 
the tour of the republics of the former Yugoslavia where 
UNPROFOR forces are stationed. President Gligorov had a meeting 
with Akashi. He also met with the Minister for Defense Vlado 
Popovski and the Minister for foreign relations, Stevo 
Crvenkovski. Akashi also visited the area of operations of 
UNPROFOR in Macedonia. Otherwise those days the mandate of the 
current commander of UNPROFOR, Brigadier-General Finn Saemark 
Thomsen, came to an end. The new commander, the Norwegian Trygve 
Tellefsch, will arrive in Macedonia on Sunday. 

</TEXT>

