<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Vojvodina </F>
<H3> <TI>   DZVM Not To Help Form New Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801094694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0822 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801094694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Novi Sad, 18 Jan (TANJUG) -- The Democratic 
Community of Vojvodina Hungarians [Demokratska Zajednica 
Vojvodjanskih Madjara -- DZVM] will not help form a new 
government in the Republic of Serbia, Andras Agaston, the 
chairman of this organization told TANJUG today. In other words 
the DZVM, with its five deputies, will not enter a coalition 
with either the Socialist Party of Serbia or the opposition. To 
a suggestion that in this case neither side will have the 
necessary 126 votes in the republican parliament, Agaston said 
that "other solutions will have to be sought." The decision not 
to take part in the formation of a new republican government was 
adopted by the DZVM presidency last Saturday. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

