<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegations in Geneva Discuss Bosnia Peace </TI></H3>
<H4>   13-Percent Proposal `Unacceptable' </H4>
<F P=102> LD1901095294 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
0900 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1901095294 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Tihomir Vinkovic from Geneva] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The Croatian standpoint with 
regard to Bosnia-Herzegovina is clear. Negotiations can take 
place on the basis of the European Council proposal dated 22 
December and the Brussels conclusions. According to these, 
Croatia should get at least 17.5 percent of the territory of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. The Muslim proposal which was given to the 
Croats yesterday goes below this -- only 13 percent. This is 
unacceptable to the Croats, it has been learned from the 
Croatian delegation. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

