<H3> <TI>   Delegations in Geneva Discuss Bosnia Peace </TI></H3>
<H4>   FRY, Croatia Agree on Relations </H4>
<F P=102> LD1901111794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1055 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1901111794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, 19 Jan (TANJUG) -- Talks between the 
delegations of the FRY and Croatia ended in Geneva this morning 
with an agreement on the normalization of mutual relations. It 
has been learned unofficially that during the day a joint 
declaration on this will be signed and made public in the Palais 
des Nations. 
  It has been learned from well-informed sources in Geneva 
that 
the two delegations agreed that representative offices of 
Croatia and the FRY will be opened in Belgrade and Zagreb. It 
has also been learned that the representative offices will be 
opened before mutual recognition is achieved. 
  As for the normalization of relations, apart from the 
opening 
of the representative offices, the opening of the 
Belgrade-Zagreb highway and telephone and telex links is also 
envisioned. 

</TEXT>

