<H4>   Supply Officers Dismissed </H4>
<F P=102> AU1501145994 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 2000 
GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1501145994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] By decree of President Zhelev, Colonel Valentin 
Nikolov Popinski was dismissed today from the post of chief of 
the Defense Ministry's Department for Supplies and Trade. Col. 
Popinski was said to have committed gross violations in 
connection with poor control of the fulfillment of contracts and 
had signed contracts unilaterally, to the detriment of the 
Defense Ministry. 
  According to the Defense Ministry announcement, for the same 
reasons Defense Minister Valentin Aleksandrov has ordered the 
dismissal from active military service on disciplinary grounds 
of Colonel Engineer Stoyan Tsvetkov Tsakov, deputy chief of the 
Department for Supplies and Trade. 

</TEXT>

