<H3> <TI>   Army Actions Against Corruption Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Minister Dismisses Housing Officer </H4>
<F P=102> AU1501182494 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1501182494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We will wage the campaign against corruption in the 
Army mercilessly and uncompromisingly -- this is the categorical 
view of Defense Minister Valentin Aleksandrov. 
  An announcement by the Defense Ministry Press Center states 
that facts have been established confirming gross violations 
during the recent allocation of housing that began on 11 
January, connected with certain people enriching themselves at 
the expense of others. 
  The announcement further states that a group of 30 officers 
from the Sofia Garrison came to see the defense minister and 
explained to him their complaints. Their complaints had also 
been deposited with the commission supervising sales at the 
Sofia Garrison. Despite explicit instructions issued by 
Minister Aleksandrov, the commission chairman, Colonel Georgi 
Vutov, adopted a rude, unceremonious attitude toward the senior 
and junior officers. The defense minister went in person to the 
place were the commission sits and immediately dismissed Colonel 
Vutov from active military service for violations in carrying 
out the duties entrusted to him. The minister also ordered the 
replacement of all the members of the commission. 

</TEXT>

