<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   ICRC Halts Banja Luka Work `Indefinitely' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1901084094 Paris AFP in English 2151 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1901084094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, Jan 18 (AFP) -- The International Committee 
of the Red Cross on Tuesday [18 January] suspended indefinitely 
its relief operations in the area of Banja Luka in Bosnia after 
an bomb destroyed one of its vehicles. A spokesman in the 
Serb-controlled town told AFP that the vehicle had been blown up 
early Tuesday outside an apartment of two ICRC employees but the 
blast caused no casualties. "This attack raises serious 
problems of security," said Pierre Gauthier, an ICRC spokesman 
in Geneva. Loyal authorities have opened an enquiry into the 
attack, the spokesman said. The ICRC has about 25 workers in 
the northwestern town, which is a base for supplying both Moslem 
and Serb populations in the area. 

</TEXT>

