<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb-Muslim Clashes Reported East of Mostar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801151994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1400 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] [Correspondent] Zdenko Vranjes reporting for 
Croatian radio. [passage omitted] 
  Mostar is quiet, but sporadic explosions can be heard from 
the foothills of Mount Velez [east of Mostar]. According to the 
Serbian media, Serbian forces have launched an artillery attack 
on Muslim positions on the foothills of Mount Velez. Radio 
Nevesinje [Serb-held town east of Mostar] reports that Serbian 
forces have responded to an artillery attack launched by the 
Muslim army on Cobanovo Polje near Nevesinje. According to this 
report, two Serbian soldiers were killed in the attack. Serbian 
military sources have reported that the Muslims are massing 
their forces on the foothills of Mount Velez. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

