<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Clinton, Visegrad Leaders Continue Prague Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   Olechowski, Zieleniec Meet </H4>
<F P=102> LD1201165794 Warsaw PAP in English 1524 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, Jan. 12 -- Polish and Czech Foreign 
Ministers Andrzej Olechowski and Josef Zieleniec stated at their 
meeting in Prague on Wednesday that the Visegrad Group continues 
to exist and that certain "misunderstandings" which occurred 
recently over the relations with NATO should have no effect on 
the Polish-Czech relations. 
  Minister Josef Zieleniec stressed that the strategic 
interest 
of the Czech Republic is to see Poland within the Western 
European structures alongside with the Czech Republic itself and 
other countries of the region. 
  Director of the Information Department in the Foreign 
Ministry Wladyslaw Klaczynski said that Polish-Czech 
consultations on building a European security structure would 
start in the near future. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

