<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peace Agreement Signed With Yugoslavia </TI></H3>
<H4>   HSP Criticizes Agreement </H4>
<F P=102> LD2001202394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1600 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2001202394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ante Djapic, vice chairman of and spokesman for the 
Croatian Party of Rights [HSP], commented at a news conference 
in Rijeka today on the decision to open an office of the 
Republic of Croatia in Belgrade and an office of the Federal 
Republic in Zagreb. 
  He said that the HSP, the Croatian Pure Party of Rights, and 
the Croatian National Democratic League are demanding the urgent 
convening of a Croatian Assembly session at which the president 
of the republic and the foreign minister should reveal all the 
circumstances under which the agreement with the FRY was signed. 
They are also calling for the rejection of all agreements with 
the FRY until the Serb occupation army withdraws from the 
territory of the Republic of Croatia and the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, until all expelled persons are allowed to 
return to their homes, and until the FRY explicitly recognizes 
the Republic of Croatia and the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina 
and their internationally recognized borders. 
  Djapic also disclosed that the merger of the three parties 
into the Croatian Party of Rights can be expected in the near 
future. 

</TEXT>

