<H3> <TI>   President Zhelev, Mitterrand Hold Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1901131694 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1300 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1901131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The 30-minute meeting between President Zhelyu 
Zhelev and French President Francois Mitterrand has ended. At 
the end of the meeting the French president told reporters that 
the purpose of his visit was to check at what stage Bulgaria's 
preparations are for hosting the Council of Europe session in 
May. 
  Another goal of his meeting is to strengthen 
Bulgarian-French 
economic and cultural relations, stressing economic contacts in 
particular. 
  The French president said that stimulating foreign 
investments is of special importance for Bulgaria. They must be 
directed with priority toward small and medium-size enterprises. 
  President Mitterrand promised to support Bulgaria's efforts 
to achieve an alleviation of the burden of foreign debt. 

</TEXT>

