<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Welcomes Nuclear Arms Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801192294 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1800 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Hungarian Foreign Ministry welcomes the 
agreement between Ukraine, Russia, and the United States on 
dismantling the nuclear weapons in the territory of Ukraine, on 
the implementation of the START I treaty. The Hungarian Foreign 
Ministry also welcomes Ukraine's determination to join the 
nuclear nonproliferation treaty as soon as possible. The step 
reduces the danger of a nuclear war, eases the tension 
prevailing in our region, and increases the chance for peace, 
the communique of the Hungarian Foreign Ministry reads. 

</TEXT>

