<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Constitutional Court Abolishes Croatian State </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2001170094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2001170094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Bosnia-Herzegovina Constitutional Court has 
decided at today's session to revoke the declaration issued in 
Livno on 24 August 1993 on the formation of the so-called 
Croatian republic of Herceg-Bosna. The Constitutional Court 
believes that this decision is not in accordance with the 
Constitution of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina, as -- in an 
unconstitutional way -- it represents an attempt to create on a 
part of the state territory of Bosnia-Herzegovina a new form of 
social-political community with the basic symbols of a state and 
legal entity. This violates in the strongest of ways the 
constitutional organization, the sovereignty, the unity, and the 
inviolability of the territory of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina as an internationally recognized country. 
This is issued in a statement by the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Constitutional Court. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

