<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by the Information Center of the Travnik War </F>
Presidency] 
  [Excerpt] Although we have been sending appeals from 
Travnik and we cannot say that they have resulted in any real 
help to our city, the fact that humanitarian situation is 
getting worse by the day obliges us to continue appealing to 
humanitarian organizations and the UNHCR, as well as to our 
country's Presidency and government. 
  There are 27,000 refugees here whom Travnik has been taking 
care of for a long time and we do not know how we are still 
managing to help them survive, but the fact that the local 
population of Travnik is also hungry and that they need 
humanitarian aid just as the refugees do should [word 
indistinct] all those people who should and must help us. The 
local population are getting food mainly in soup kitchens where 
food reserves are only sufficient for a few days. [passage 
omitted] 

