Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 19 Jan (TANJUG) -- At today's session 
chaired by Prime Minister Radoje Kontic, the Federal Yugoslav 
Government adopted the text of the joint declaration on the 
normalization of relations between the Federal Republic of 
Yugoslavia [FRY] and the Republic of Croatia. The declaration 
also envisages the opening of the two governments' missions -- 
an office of the FRY in Zagreb and an office of the Republic of 
Croatia in Belgrade, the Federal Information Ministry has 
disclosed. 
