<H3> <TI>   ATA: Accusation Unsubstantiated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1501182694 Tirana ATA in English 1309 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1501182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, January 15 (ATA) -- Officials of the 
Socialist Party [SP] have told ATA that they intended to provide 
clarification of their accusation that ATA was blocking news 
about the opposition parties in Albania. The SP statement was 
made by the SP vice chairman, Servet Pellumbi, and Deputy 
Bashkim Zeneli on January 10, who said that a further 
declaration on the subject would be forthcoming the next day. 
  However, Mr. Zeneli subsequently informed our reporter that 
the SP had not yet marshalled the data to substantiate their 
charges. Several days have now passed without further word from 
the SP. 

</TEXT>

