<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   ATA Director Urges Media To Be Constructive </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1501183094 Tirana ATA in English 1119 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1501183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, January 15 (ATA) -- The commission of 
socialist intelligentsia sponsored a meeting January 14 at which 
reporters from the Radio-TV, the ALBANIAN TELEGRAPHIC AGENCY 
[ATA] and other representatives of the mass media exchanged 
opinions on professional and ethical aspects of journalism. The 
discussion aimed at avoiding banalities and politicization in 
the media. 
  Ilir Zhilla, director of ATA, stressed that ATA is a great 
national asset for the mass media and called on all press organs 
to use information available from ATA (some 3,000 items of world 
news a day) and information provided by ATA's district 
correspondents. 
  Mr. Zhilla asked his colleagues to respect each other and 
the 
organizations for which they work. He said that reporters 
should avoid hostile polemics and declared that the Albanian 
news media should maintain constructive policies in order to 
encourage the people and the political leadership in overcoming 
the difficulties of the transition period. Mr. Zhilla also 
sternly criticized irresponsibility and damage to the national 
interest on the part of the press. 

</TEXT>

