<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Explains Fuel Price Decision </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1401200294 Tirana ATA in English 1105 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1401200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, January 14 (ATA) -- The Albanian Government 
took recently a decision for the increase of the price of fuels 
which comes into force January 16, 1993. The proposal for this 
increase was presented by the Ministry of Finance and Ministry 
of Mining and Energy Resources. 
  The price of one ton of crude oil will increase from 4,500 
leks to 6,500 leks, a liter benzine [gasoline] from 34 to 46 
leks and imported benzine from 62 leks per liter to 82 leks, 
while the price of gasoil will increase from 25 leks to 38 leks 
per liter and the price of natural gas from 3,000 leks to 6,300 
leks per 1,000 cubic meter. According to Niqifor Rexho, 
director of Finance Department at the Ministry of Mineral and 
Energy Resources, there is a program which intends to bring the 
prices of oil and its by products to the level of prices in the 
neighbouring countries. According to Mr. Rexho, the price of 
crude oil is expected to amount to $80 per ton. 

</TEXT>

