<H3> <TI>   Civilian Control Over Military Preserved </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701175594 Warsaw PAP in English 1647 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, Jan. 17 -- First Deputy Defence Minister 
Jerzy Milewski told journalists on Monday that civilian control 
over the armed forces will be preserved despite the planned 
changes in the Polish Defence Ministry. 
  Opinions that the Defence Ministry is ceding its 
prerogatives 
to the general staff are untrue, Milewski declared. 
  He described the planned changes as "corrections in the 
organizational structure" designed to precisely define the tasks 
and improve the work of the Defence Ministry and the general 
staff. 
  According to Milewski the changes are also meant to reduce 
the excessively large administration. 
  Milewski also stressed that it was "indispensable" for the 
civilian Defence Ministry's departments at present to employ the 
military. "There are not so many military experts among 
civilians now," he said. 

</TEXT>

