<F P=101> Yugoslavia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kosovo </TI></H3>
<H4>   ATA: Kosovo Charges `Obviously Trumped Up' </H4>
<F P=102> AU1501163494 Tirana ATA in English 1113 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1501163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, January 15 (ATA) -- Four Albanians were 
brought before the Serbian court of the Peje District on January 
14 on obviously trumped up political charges. The accused are: 
Fisnik Ukaj, 25, from Peje, chairman of the Independent 
Students' Union of Prishtina University; Sadri Shala, 61, 
mechanic from Ujmir of Kline; Ymer Shala, 29, mechanic; and Ali 
Lajqi, deputy of the Kosova parliament and a former political 
prisoner. The first three are charged with "carrying out 
hostile activity and violation of territorial integrity" of 
former Yugoslavia and the fourth with knowledge of a criminal 
act and failure to inform the authorities. All of the accused 
are charged with participating in a meeting in Ujmir village of 
Kline in October 1991 for the purpose of forming an people's 
organization for the Republic of Kosova." 
  The accused denied the charges considering them groundless. 
They also claimed that they had been tortured before their 
imprisonment. The trial has been adjourned until January 28. 

</TEXT>

