resolving the problems in which the possibilities and facilities 
are more present for both sides to contribute to programmed 
cooperation. 
  In these meetings, Mr. Papandoniou stressed once more the 
importance of the fact that Greece will head the EC presidency 
for six months. He mentioned the sum of 350 million [as heard] 
ECU that the EC has planned to provide for transports and 
infrastructure during this year. During the talks, they spoke 
about the possibilities of providing financial support to 
Albanian transportation in general. 
  The Greek side also presented concrete projects to Mr. 
Bitincka, assuring him of the Greek Government's support for 
companies that may invest to improve the Albanian 
transportation. The delegation continues its visit in Tirana. 

