<H3> <TI>   Greek Minister Visits, Meets With Officials </TI></H3>
<H4>   Visit Seen as `Concrete Step' </H4>
<F P=102> AU2001093094 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1900 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2001093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The meeting held this afternoon between Foreign 
Minister Alfred Serreqi and Ioannis Papandoniou, Greek alternate 
national economy minister, assessed Papandoniou's visit to 
Tirana, following that of Papoulias some time ago, as a concrete 
step toward implementation of economic cooperation between both 
countries, in the framework of an atmosphere of good cooperation 
that is in the interest not only of Albania and Greece but also 
of our turbulent region. 
  The existence of the Greek minority in Albania and of 
Albanian refugees in Greece are circumstances that favor this 
cooperation and ease bilateral understanding. Mr. Serreqi 
stressed that, viewed from a judicial aspect and considering the 
resources it possesses, Albania, which has made concrete steps 
toward a market economy, sees as a favorable circumstance the 
fact that Greece, as the only Balkan country near the EC and 
being the EC president for the current six-month period, can 
possibly influence Albania's concrete engagement in EC economic 
projects. 

</TEXT>

