<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Welcomes FRY-Croatian Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2101074294 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2101074294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Romanian Ministry of Foreign Affairs welcomes 
the signing in Geneva of an understanding between the Federal 
Republic of Yugoslavia and the Republic of Croatia on relations 
between the two countries. 
  The Romanian Foreign Ministry issued a communique in which 
it 
expresses the belief that the positive development registered in 
the relations between the two countries represents an important 
and encouraging moment which will make a substantial 
contribution and provide an impetus to the peace process in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, reduce tension, and create conditions for a 
new consensus on coexistence in the area of the former 
Yugoslavia. 
  As a matter of fact, this moment is in line with the 
constant 
position promoted by Romania, which is to stimulate the process 
of normalizing relations between all countries that have emerged 
in the area of the former Yugoslavia and to hold talks between 
them. 
  The Romanian Foreign Ministry, reads the communique, 
expresses the hope that this process will continue and, thus, 
contribute to the promotion of political stability in this area 
and in the entire region. 

</TEXT>

