<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council of Europe Official on Minorities Policy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2401081494 Bratislava REPUBLIKA in Slovak 20 Jan 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2401081494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava REPUBLIKA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Aspects of Human Rights; M.A. Martinez </F>
Received by Leading Representatives of the Slovak Republic"] 
  [Excerpts] Bratislava -- [passage omitted] Slovak 
Parliament Chairman Ivan Gasparovic received Miguel Angel 
Martinez, president of the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council 
of Europe, in the early evening yesterday. Their talks 
concerned primarily aspects of human and civic rights of 
individuals and national communities, the ratification of the 
Slovak Republic's agreement on association with the European 
Union [EU] by the parliaments of EU member states, and the 
Partnership for Peace project. [passage omitted] 
  At a briefing held after the meeting, Miguel Angel Martinez 
reiterated his conviction that Slovakia is a country respecting 
the freedom of citizens and their right of assembly. The 
Komarno rally [of representatives of the Hungarian minority on 8 
January 1994] is a proof of this. Ivan Gasparovic stressed the 
fact that M.A. Martinez had declared his visit as a working trip 
to one of the member countries of the Council of Europe and not 
as an inspection. 
  The highest representative of the National Council of the 
Slovak Republic briefed his guest about the territorial and 
administrative division of Slovakia currently under preparation 
and about Slovakia's rejection of the [Hungarian minority 
representatives'] project of the country's division on the basis 
of the ethnic principle. He also spoke with him about planned 
legislation addressing the issue of designating the names of 
communities in the language of ethnic minorities and the writing 
of their names and surnames. The president of the Parliamentary 
Assembly of the Council of Europe showed understanding for this 
approach. [passage omitted] 
  Later in the evening, at the end of the first day of the 
Council of Europe Parliamentary Assembly delegation's stay in 
Slovakia, Miguel Angel Martinez was received by Slovak Prime 
Minister Vladimir Meciar. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

