<H3> <TI>   Government To Purchase More Arms From Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101210894 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2101210894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Within the framework of reducing debts owed to 
Slovakia by the former Soviet Union, Slovakia will purchase 
military equipment in Russia to the tune of between $80 and $90 
million. This was stated by Igor Urban, state secretary of the 
Slovak Defense Ministry, following his talks with Russian 
officials in Moscow. According to him, experts from both 
countries will discuss in the weeks to follow the precise amount 
and kind of equipment to be purchased. Igor Urban, who signed a 
plan for military cooperation between the Slovak and Russian 
Defense Ministries in Moscow today, remarked that at issue was 
equipment that the Slovak Armed Forces will use in the current 
year. 

</TEXT>

