<H3> <TI>   Government Adopts Decision on Granic Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201154794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1437 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2201154794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 22 Jan (TANJUG)--At its session on 21 
January, the Government of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia 
adopted a decision on the meeting between Federal Deputy Prime 
Minister Zeljko Simic and Mate Granic, deputy prime minister and 
foreign minister of the Republic of Croatia, scheduled for 27 
January in Geneva, the Federal Information Ministry announced 
today. The representatives of the Yugoslav and Croatian 
Governments will discuss topical humanitarian issues, as well as 
possibilities for the further normalization of Yugoslav-Croatian 
relations that will not prejudge a final political solution, the 
announcement says. 

