<H3> <TI>   Milosevic, Opposition Discuss Unity Government </TI></H3>
<H4>   Radicals Reject Meeting </H4>
<F P=102> LD2101170694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1623 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2101170694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 21 Jan (TANJUG) -- Tomislav Nikolic, 
deputy chairman of the Serbian Radical Party [SRS], announced 
today that he refused to attend a meeting with Serbian President 
Slobodan Milosevic. A statement dispatched to TANJUG says that 
along with some other leaders of the opposition, Nikolic was 
invited to meet the president of the republic today, and that 
the meeting was scheduled to take place at 1600. "I refused to 
go to his office because I have nothing to discuss with Slobodan 
Milosevic as long as state television imposes a blockade on the 
SRS," the statement by the SRS deputy chairman says. 

</TEXT>

