<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Discusses Election of Speaker </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401104494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1022 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401104494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 24 Jan (TANJUG) -- Following the unanimous 
election of a 15-strong approval committee, on the basis of 
whose report the Serbian Assembly is to approve today the 
mandates of 250 deputies elected on 19 December last year, 
Vojislav Dimitrijevic, chairman of the constitutive session, 
called a break until 1400. At the same time, he called on the 
deputies to submit in writing their reasoned proposals for the 
new speaker of the parliament, who is to be elected today. 
Thirty deputies can propose a candidate for the speaker. 

