<H3> <TI>   Archbishop Rejects Tudjman's Bosnia Policy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2101191894 Vienna ORF Television Network in German 1830 
GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2101191894 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna ORF Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Zagreb Archbishop Franjo Kuharic has criticized 
Croatian President Tudjman's policy. The cardinal clearly 
rejected the division of Bosnia-Herzegovina. If a change of 
Bosnia's borders by force were permitted, the borders of Croatia 
and other countries would no longer be inviolable either. The 
church is calling for a peace that does justice to all 
nationalities, explained the cardinal, who sharply condemned 
anti-Semitic media reports in Croatia only a few days ago. 

</TEXT>

